0the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20Health%2C%20developed%20an%20interest%20in%20brain-computer%20interfaces%20while%20working%20as%20an%20electrical%20engineer.%3Cp%3ECarrie%20Pitzer%2FMichigan%20Medicine%2C%20University%20of%20Michigan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMatthew%20Willsey%20led%20a%20team%20of%20doctors%20for%20Paradromics'%20first%20long-term%20brain%20chip%20implant.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWillsey%20first%20became%20interested%20in%20brain-computer%20interfaces%20while%20studying%20electrical%20engineering.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20brain-chip%20surgery%20must%20become%20routine%20before%20the%20technology%20can%20scale.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Matthew%20Willsey%2C%20a%20neurosurgeon%20who%20specializes%20in%20brain-computer%20interfaces.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20became%20a%20neurosurgeon%2C%20I%20was%20an%20electrical%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20graduated%20from%20MIT%20with%20my%20undergraduate%20degree%20and%20pursued%20my%20master's%20in%20electrical%20engineering.%20I%20did%20my%20thesis%20with%20Alan%20Oppenheim%2C%20a%20professor%20who%20helped%20pioneer%20the%20field%20of%20digital%20signal%20processing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESignal%20processing%20looks%20at%20how%20to%20extract%20information%20from%20signals.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20that's%20similar%20to%20what%20we%20do%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrain-computer-interface-what-is-it-how-does-it-work-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebrain-computer%20interfaces%20(BCIs)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%202009%2C%20I%20saw%20a%20video%20of%20someone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrain-computer-chip-link-interface-neurotech-human-trial-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtrolling%20a%20computer%3C%2Fa%3E%20cursor%20or%20robotic%20arm%20with%20electrodes%20implanted%20into%20their%20brain%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20the%20coolest%20thing%20I've%20ever%20seen%20in%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20epiphany%20moment%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20soon%20shadowed%20a%20neurosurgeon%20in%20Texas.%20The%20combination%20of%20seeing%20BCIs%20and%20then%20seeing%20surgery%20convinced%20me%20that%20neurosurgery%20was%20the%20right%20career%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20school%20at%20Baylor%20College%20of%20Medicine%2C%20then%20matched%20into%20a%20neurosurgery%20residency%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan.%20I%20spent%20three%20years%20doing%20research%20and%20completed%20a%20Ph.D.%2C%20focused%20on%20BCIs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20my%20practice%20is%20in%20functional%20neurosurgery%2C%20with%20a%20specialty%20in%20deep%20brain%20stimulation%20and%20epilepsy.%20I%20also%20have%20a%20research%20lab%20that%20studies%20BCIs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Matthew%20Willsey%20and%20the%20Paradromics%20team%20connect%20and%20test%20the%20device%20components.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3b16926891755ad48b8401%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225034%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWillsey%20and%20the%20Paradromics%20team%20connect%20and%20test%20the%20device%20components.%3Cp%3ECarrie%20Pitzer%2FMichigan%20Medicine%2C%20University%20of%20Michigan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20diseases%20and%20injuries%20in%20which%20the%20brain%20is%20largely%20functioning%20fine.%20People%20know%20how%20they%20want%20to%20move%20or%20what%20they%20want%20to%20say%2C%20but%20the%20pathway%20connecting%20the%20brain%20to%20the%20body%20or%20the%20mouth%20is%20interrupted%20or%20degraded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findu-navar-nonprofit-everything-als-ai-tech-silicon-valley-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESomeone%20with%20ALS%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20knows%20what%20words%20they%20want%20to%20say%2C%20but%20they%20can't%20produce%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20BCI%20tries%20to%20record%20brain%20activity%2C%20recognize%20patterns%2C%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20someone%20intends%20to%20do.%20Then%2C%20you%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-brain-chip-implant-first-human-patient-what-its-like-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eput%20text%20on%20a%20screen%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20provide%20a%20control%20signal%20to%20a%20robotic%20arm%20or%20a%20computer%20cursor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparadromics-brain-chip-implant-first-human-patient-speech-restoration-bci-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EParadromics%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20designed%20to%20be%20fully%20implantable.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20BCIs%20used%20in%20research%20labs%20before%20were%20implanted%20into%20the%20brain%2C%20but%20they%20had%20a%20connection%20that%20passed%20through%20the%20skin%2C%20so%20they%20could%20connect%20to%20a%20computer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20build%20these%20devices%20at%20scale%2C%20ideally%2C%20you%20want%20fully%20implantable%20systems.%20People%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20tethered%20to%20a%20computer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245074f94-e7c8-498b-8b37-acc825647f46%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20procedure%20should%20be%20repeatable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20process%20is%20built%20on%20careful%20patient%20selection.%20You%20want%20someone%20who%20has%20enough%20impairment%20that%20they%20could%20benefit%2C%20but%20not%20so%20much%20impairment%20that%20it%20makes%20surgery%20unsafe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20surgery%2C%20we%20started%20with%20the%20cranial%20portion.%20We%20made%20an%20incision%2C%20took%20the%20bone%20off%2C%20opened%20the%20dura%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lining%20around%20the%20brain%20%E2%80%94%20and%20exposed%20the%20cortex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20our%20navigational%20system%2C%20our%20own%20sight%2C%20and%20preoperative%20imaging%2C%20we%20can%20identify%20the%20exact%20location%20where%20we%20want%20to%20place%20the%20array%20or%20implant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20monitor%20shows%20a%20scan%20of%20a%20patient's%20brain.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3b15f36891755ad48b83fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222999%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWillsey%20uses%20live-imaging%20navigational%20equipment%20to%20plan%20the%20implant%20site.%3Cp%3ECarrie%20Pitzer%2FMichigan%20Medicine%2C%20University%20of%20Michigan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20array%20is%20gently%20placed%20onto%20the%20brain%20and%20then%20inserted%20into%20the%20cortex.%20After%20we%20secured%20the%20lead%2C%20closed%20the%20dura%2C%20and%20put%20the%20bone%20back%20in%20place%2C%20we%20made%20an%20incision%20in%20the%20chest%20for%20the%20transceiver.%20An%20extension%20lead%20runs%20under%20the%20skin%20from%20the%20brain%20component%20down%20to%20the%20chest%20component.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20leaving%20the%20operating%20room%2C%20you%20want%20to%20know%20that%20the%20electrodes%20are%20in%20the%20brain%2C%20bleeding%20has%20stopped%2C%20the%20tissues%20are%20closed%20appropriately%2C%20and%20the%20whole%20system%20is%20communicating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-elon-musk-expanding-production-brain-chips-automated-procedure-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20procedure%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself%20takes%20about%20four%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%20is%20not%20that%20technically%20different%20from%20a%20surgical%20standpoint.%20Neurosurgeons%20know%20how%20to%20perform%20a%20craniotomy%20and%20access%20the%20brain.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20scale%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrain-chips-elon-musk-neuralink-change-personality-behavior-computer-tech-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBCI%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20want%20neurosurgeons%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pick%20it%20up%20very%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hope%20is%20that%2C%20as%20we%20perform%20these%20procedures%2C%20they%20become%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281999343-52d3-4b51-9ac4-0d431e233759%5C%22%3EThis%20surgery%20takes%20the%20next%20step%20forward%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20surgery%20felt%20like%20business%20as%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20times%20when%20you%20would%20take%20a%20step%20back%2C%20when%20you're%20placing%20the%20array%20over%20the%20cortex%2C%20and%20think%3A%20Okay%2C%20here%20we%20go.%20This%20will%20be%20a%20major%20step%20forward%20if%20we%20can%20get%20everything%20working%20correctly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222892%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20doctor%20holds%20a%20device%20in%20their%20hands.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3b16f53d84808d83754c21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222169%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWillsey%20holds%20the%20transceiver%20before%20implanting%20it%20in%20the%20participant's%20chest.%3Cp%3EUniversity%20of%20Michigan%20and%20Paradromics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20you%20have%20to%20get%20back%20into%20the%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFundamentally%2C%20every%20surgeon%20is%20mostly%20focused%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-first-remote-robotic-brain-surgery-da-vinci-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epatient%20safety%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Once%20the%20patient%20wakes%20up%2C%20you%20do%20the%20postoperative%20exam.%20When%20the%20patient%20is%20doing%20well%2C%20then%20you%20can%20really%20take%20a%20step%20back%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWow%2C%20I%20can't%20believe%20we're%20at%20this%20point%20now%20where%20we%20have%20somebody%20implanted%20with%20a%20novel%20brain-computer%20interface.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%2