0work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20an%20interview%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BTwenty%20Minute%20VC%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflexport-upskilling-ai-employee-program-product-engineering-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECEO%20of%20Flexport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20global%20freight%20forwarding%20and%20customs%20brokerage%20company%2C%20said%20his%20firm%20will%20likely%20keep%20staffing%20headcount%20flat%20while%20spending%20more%20on%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20expects%20employees%20to%20clock%20in%20at%20the%20office%2C%20and%20didn't%20mince%20words%20describing%20what%20he%20thought%20about%20remote%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%20in%20the%20interview%2C%20Petersen%20called%20remote%20work%20%26quot%3Bwhite%20collar%20fraud%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20citing%20workday%20distractions%20and%20a%20decay%20in%20workplace%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20three-year-old%20and%20a%20five-year-old.%20The%20idea%20that%20I%20could%20do%20any%20work%20at%20my%20house%20is%20like%20a%20total%20fantasy%2C%26quot%3B%20Petersen%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%2C%20like%2C%20I%20have%20a%20bigger%20house%20than%20most%20employees%20do.%20Like%2C%20I%20actually%20do%20have%20a%20private%20office%20I%20can%20close%20the%20door%20on.%20It%20doesn't%20matter%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20no%20work%20getting%20done%20at%20that%20house%20when%20the%20kids%20are%20around.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20remote%20work%20debate%2C%20Petersen%20also%20touched%20on%20another%20growing%20tension%20in%20businesses%20today%3A%20executives%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-coo-andrew-macdonald-ai-token-spending-harder-justify-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epouring%20money%20into%20AI%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20one%20day%20automate%20expensive%20white-collar%20tasks%2C%20while%20also%20redefining%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcfo-power-brokers-ai-era-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehuman%20roles%20matter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20their%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetersen%20said%20Flexport%20is%20spending%20about%20%245%20million%20a%20year%20on%20AI%20models.%20When%20asked%20whether%20that%20could%20rise%20to%20%2420%20million%20in%20five%20years%2C%20he%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bpossible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20CEO%20said%20his%20company%2C%20which%20currently%20employs%20just%20under%202%2C000%20people%2C%20could%20maintain%20the%20same%20head%20count%20in%20three%20or%20four%20years%2C%20because%20he%20needs%20humans%20that%20are%20good%20at%20sales%20and%20using%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20every%20business%20on%20the%20planet%20that%20needs%20to%20ship%20something%20anywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20boots%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20you%20want%20to%20just%20to%20interface%20with%20those%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20some%20employees%20doing%20manual%20operations%20work%20would%20need%20to%20move%20into%20more%20customer-facing%20roles%2C%20such%20as%20sales%20and%20account%20management.%20If%20they%20cannot%20make%20that%20shift%2C%20he%20said%2C%20Flexport%20may%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Brebalance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia-based%20Flexport%20%E2%80%94%20which%20became%20one%20of%20the%20highest-profile%20logistics%20startups%20during%20the%20pandemic-era%20supply-chain%20crunch%20and%20has%20raised%20money%20from%20investors%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-palmer-luckey-bryan-johnson-tech-play-mafia-show-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPeter%20Thiel's%20Founders%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Google%20Ventures%20%E2%80%94%20uses%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%2C%20Petersen%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20firm's%20spending%20on%20AI%20models%20has%20doubled%20in%20recent%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20still%20bullish%20on%20the%20tech%2C%20despite%20the%20growing%20line%20item.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20things%20are%20just%20incredible%2C%20miraculous%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20worry%20about%20is%20that%20they%20cut%20us%20off%20and%20then%20we%20can't%20use%20it%20anymore.%20And%20like%2C%20if%20I%20can't%20use%20OpenAI%2C%20we're%20all%20just%20going%20to%20go%20back%20to%20being%20idiots%20we%20were%20two%20years%20ago.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221cdf945d-3e88-440d-9d58-07407a47ab7e%5C%22%3EThe%20internet%20responds%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPetersen's%20comments%20about%20remote%20work%20struck%20a%20nerve%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20pushback%20to%20Petersen's%20remarks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FLinusEkenstam%2Fstatus%2F2069050966901494232%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecame%20from%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20said%20they%20often%20rely%20on%20remote%20work%20to%20manage%20caregiving%20responsibilities.%20Several%20said%20working%20from%20home%20allows%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FCarmenDecouto%2Fstatus%2F2069118964354163164%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edevelop%20better%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20their%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.x.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EI%E2%80%99ve%20been%20on%20a%20webinar%20breastfeeding%20a%2010%20week%20old%2C%20ran%20an%20all%20hands%20with%20a%20four%20year%20old%20literally%20climbing%20my%20shoulders%2C%20shipped%20code%20with%20a%20baby%20in%20a%20carrier%2C%20podcasted%20w%20a%20quiet%209%20year%20old%20in%20the%20corner%2C%20approve%20PRs%20while%20doing%20the%20sleep%20lady%20shuffle%20(iykyk)%2C%20skill%20issue.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2